  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Hemolysis predictions are benchmarked against the relative hemolysis index (RH < 1) acceptance criterion derived from predicate device comparisons. The turbulence-induced erythrocyte damage model employed in this assessment follows the power-law formulation documented in the peer-reviewed methodology survey referenced herein.",
